before sourcing, you need download the zip file and extract it to your working directory.
Sourcing the run_analysis.R then you will get data.frame called tidydata which is my final tidy data set.

column "Activity" indicated the data is collected from which of the 6 different activities
(WALKING, WALKING_UPSTAIRS, WALKING_DOWNSTAIRS, SITTING, STANDING, LAYING).

column "Subject" indicated the data is collected from which of the 30 different subjects.

other columns give averge of corresponding data for different signals.
